comments.body:
Hi David - 

Doesn't actually work.  A given excludedSubtree is not mated to any specific permittedSubtree.  The name acceptance logic is something like:

if (excludedSubtrees exist) {
  if (any excludedSubtrees match the name) THEN {
     reject;
  } 
}
if (includedSubtrees exist) {
   if (any includedSubtrees match the name) then {
     accept;
   } 
  reject;
}
accept;

Mike

@mstjohns, thanks for submitting your suggestions as a PR. Your changes look good from a content standpoint, but the doc build pipeline is complaining about trailing whitespace on the following lines:

```
 106:In the pseudo-code below, 'mask' is short hand for the bit string formed from the mask portion of a constraint (e.g. the last 1/2 of the constraint octets), 
136:This section describes the Path Validation Processing specific to OtherName.MACAddress constraints.  
138:The following is a utility function used to determine whether or not 
194:foreach ( constraint rst in tempRequestedSubtrees) { 
195:    foreach ( constraint pst in prevSubtrees) { 
196:          if (childIncludedInParent (rst, pst) {  
200:     } 
208:#### Union Operation 
234:        matches = true; 
```

Can you remove this whitespace, or should I take care of it in a subsequent PR?

```suggestion
     the NameConstraints Extension in the current certificate };
```
